<br>
What is considered 'engaged' when it comes to 'end game' mobs?  Recently my guild had a fairly clear shot at Lodizal, but decided not to engage him until our tank team arrived.  <br>
<br>
During that time, someone from another guild began to 'kite' Lodizal around until his guild arrived.  Needless to say, we chose not to interrupt their 'title' to this spawn but my questions are:<br>
<br>
Is kiting considered 'possession' of a mob even if you don't have the force in the zone to kill it? &lt;IE: they had a single guildie kiting it while his team zoned in&gt;<br>
<br>
And, in relation to the above:<br>
<br>
If guild XX is kiting Lodizal and you have the force to tank Lodizal, are you entitled to kill it despite the fact that it's already engaged?  In essence, if you have the force to take it and the other guild does not, but is kiting to deny you the spawn... what is considered 'good form'?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for any replies, just trying to learn the 'high end game' political situation. <p><br>
